The paper discusses a machine learning approach to implementing the active inference framework for cognitive architecture and control policies. The paper focuses on computer vision and image processing, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.RO).
